<item>
            <title>[PIG-3017] Pig&apos;s object serialization should use compression</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3017</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have run into cases of very large JobConf objects, and part of this is the fact that serialized objects are quite large. There is no reason not to use compression here, and ratios should be quite high.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12614059">PIG-3017</key>
            <summary>Pig&apos;s object serialization should use compression</summary>
